---
import VizPlaceholder from '../VizPlaceholder.astro';

const needsInfra = [
  {
    name: 'Cross-repo reach',
    body: 'needs a graph of how every repo relates, kept current across the org.',
  },
  {
    name: 'Multiplayer',
    body: 'needs a shared, live view that many people and agents read and write at once.',
  },
  {
    name: 'Durable sessions',
    body: 'need storage that outlives the machine a session started on.',
  },
  {
    name: 'Memory',
    body: 'needs durable, searchable storage of what past sessions did, retrievable by the next one.',
  },
];
---

<section id="infrastructure" class="px-6 py-20 md:py-28">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl">
    <p class="font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.25em] text-accent">
      Where it runs
    </p>
    <h2
      class="mt-4 text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-neutral-50 sm:text-4xl"
    >
      Infrastructure
    </h2>
    <p class="mt-6 text-lg leading-relaxed text-neutral-300">
      Some of these features are local. Harness swapping and per-session setup
      can run on your machine. Others cannot. Cross-repo reach, multiplayer,
      durable sessions, and shared memory each need
      <mark>state that outlives one session and one user</mark>, which means
      infrastructure behind them.
    </p>

    <dl class="mt-8 space-y-4">
      {
        needsInfra.map((item) => (
          <div class="flex flex-col gap-1 border-t border-neutral-900 pt-4 sm:flex-row sm:gap-4">
            <dt class="shrink-0 text-base font-medium text-neutral-100 sm:w-44">
              {item.name}
            </dt>
            <dd class="text-base leading-relaxed text-neutral-400">
              {item.body}
            </dd>
          </div>
        ))
      }
    </dl>
  </div>

  <div class="mx-auto mt-14 max-w-5xl">
    <VizPlaceholder label="capability tiles sorting themselves into two columns, local vs needs-infrastructure" />
  </div>
</section>
